= Check Sequence Files Status =
#context: sop
#type: node

"""Visualizes sequence file status as point geometry showing size and modification time."""

== Overview ==

Check Sequence Files Status generates a point cloud where each point represents one frame of a file sequence. Points are colored and positioned to visualize file size (relative to the min/max across all frames) and modification time (relative to now).

Non-existent files are colored red and added to the `non_exist` point group.

[Image:opdef:.?check__seq__files.png]

TIP:
    Useful point attributes include: `size`, `mod_time`, `frame`, `file_path`, `exists`. Point groups: `size`, `time`, `non_exist`.

@parameters

Files:
    #id: files
    File path pattern for the sequence. Supports `$F` frame substitution.

Start/End:
    #id: frame_range
    Frame range to check.

Preview Length:
    #id: preview_length
    Spread of generated points along the X axis.

Preview Height:
    #id: preview_height
    Spread of generated points along the Y axis.

Font Size:
    #id: font_size
    Size of the guide text displayed in the viewport.
